 3 code]]\n| blank4_info_sec1       = HU232\n| blank5_name_sec2       = [[List of members of the National Assembly of Hungary (2018\u201322)|MP]]\n| blank5_info_sec2       = [[L\u00e1szl\u00f3 Sz\u00e1szfalvi]] ([[KDNP]])\n| website                = \n}}\n\n'''Z\u00e1k\u00e1nyfalu''' is a village in located in the [[Csurg\u00f3 District]] of [[Somogy County]], [[Hungary]].\n\n==History==\nFormerly part of [[Z\u00e1k\u00e1ny]], Z\u00e1k\u00e1nyfalu became an independent village since October 20, 2002. The northern part of the settlement took up the name Z\u00e1k\u00e1nyfalu. In the village there were 537 people in 2007 and a total of 238 apartments.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.teszir.hu/?module=objektumlista/agglomeracio&page=23|title=Agglomer\u00e1ci\u00f3s telep\u00fcl\u00e9sr\u00e9szek|publisher=teszir.hu|accessdate=2015-11-16}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{commons category|Z\u00e1k\u00e1nyfalu}}\n\n{{Csurg\u00f3 District}}\n{{Somogy}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zakanyfalu}}\n[[Category:Populated places in Somogy County]]\n\n\n{{Somogy-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement <!--more fields are available for this Infobox--See Template:Infobox Settlement-->\n| official_name          = Z\u00e1k\u00e1nyfalu\n| settlement_type        = Village\n| image_skyline          = Aerial photograph of Z\u00e1k\u00e1nyfalu.jpg\n| image_caption          = Zichy Mansion in Z\u00e1k\u00e1nyfalu\n| image_flag             = \n| image_shield           = HUN_Z\u00e1k\u00e1nyfalu_COA.jpg\n| nickname               = \n| pushpin_map            = Hungary\n| pushpin_map_caption    = Location of Gy\u00f6ngy\u00f6spata in Hungary\n| coordinates            = {{coord|46|16|1|N|16|57|33|E|region:HU|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type       = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n| subdivision_name       = {{HUN}}\n| subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Hungary|Region]]\n| subdivision_name1      = [[Southern Transdanubia]]\n| subdivision_type2   