{"title_page": "J\u00e1nos Vajda (poet)", "text_new": "{{About|the composer|the Hungarian composer|J\u00e1nos Vajda (composer)}}\n{{eastern name order|Vajda J\u00e1nos}}\n{{Infobox person\n|name = J\u00e1nos Vajda\n|image = Vajda J\u00e1nos Bruck.jpg\n|birth_date = {{birth date|1827|5|7|df=yes}}\n|birth_place = [[Pest, Hungary|Pest]], [[Kingdom of Hungary]]\n|death_date = {{death date and age|1897|1|17|1827|5|7|df=yes}}\n|death_place = [[Budapest]], [[Austria-Hungary]]\n|nationality = [[Hungarians|Hungarian]] \n|occupation = Poet, journalist\n}}\n'''J\u00e1nos Vajda''' (7 May 1827 \u2013 18 January 1897) was a Hungarian poet and journalist. His first poetry was published to the public in ''[[\u00c9letk\u00e9pek]]'' in 1844.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.babelmatrix.org/works/hu-all/Vajda_J%C3%A1nos/biography|title=Babel Web Anthology :: The page of Vajda J\u00e1nos, English biography|work=babelmatrix.org|accessdate=20 October 2015}}</ref>  He was a member of the [[Kisfaludy Society]].<ref>Szinnyei, J\u00f3zsef: ''[http://mek.oszk.hu/00300/00355/html/ABC16241/16294.htm Magyar \u00edr\u00f3k \u00e9lete \u00e9s munk\u00e1i XIV. (Telg\u00e1rti\u2013Zsutai)].'' Budapest. Horny\u00e1nszky. 1914.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{commons category-inline|J\u00e1nos Vajda}}\n\n{{Hungarian literature}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vajda, Janos}}\n[[Category:1827 births]]\n[[Category:1897 deaths]]\n[[Category:19th-century Hungarian poets]]\n[[Category:Hungarian male poets]]\n[[Category:19th-century Hungarian male writers]]\n\n\n{{Hungary-writer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{About|the composer|the Hungarian composer|J\u00e1nos Vajda (composer)}}\n{{eastern name order|Vajda J\u00e1nos}}\n{{Infobox person\n|name = J\u00e1nos Vajda\n|image = Vajda J\u00e1nos Bruck.jpg\n|birth_date = {{birth date|1827|5|7|df=yes}}\n|birth_place = [[Pest, Hungary|Pest]], [[Kingdom of Hungary]]\n|death_date = {{death date and age|1897|1|17|1827|5|7|df=yes}}\n|death_place = [[Budapest]], [[Austria-Hungary]]\n|nationality = [[Hungarians|Hungarian]] \n|occupation = Poet, journalist\n}}\n'''J\u00e1nos Vajda''' (7 May 1827 \u2013 18 January 1897) was a Hungarian poet and journalist. His first poetry was published to the public in ''[[\u00c9letk\u00e9pek]]'' in 1844.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.babelmatrix.org/works/hu-all/Vajda_J%C3%A1nos/biography|title=Babel Web Anthology :: The page of Vajda J\u00e1nos, English biography|work=babelmatrix.org|accessdate=20 October 2015}}</ref>  He was a member of the [[Kisfaludy Society]].<ref>Szinnyei, J\u00f3zsef: ''[http://mek.oszk.hu/00300/00355/html/ABC16241/16294.htm Magyar \u00edr\u00f3k \u00e9lete \u00e9s munk\u00e1i XIV. (Telg\u00e1rti\u2013Zsutai)].'' Budapest. Horny\u00e1nszky. 1914.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{commons category inline|J\u00e1nos Vajda}}\n\n{{Hungarian literature}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vajda, Janos}}\n[[Category:1827 births]]\n[[Category:1897 deaths]]\n[[Category:19th-century Hungarian poets]]\n[[Category:Hungarian male poets]]\n[[Category:19th-century male writers]]\n\n\n{{Hungary-writer-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Bearcat", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:recat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/J%C3%A1nos_Vajda_(poet)"}
