ap            = Hungary\n| pushpin_label_position = <!-- the position of the pushpin label: left, right, top, bottom, none -->\n| pushpin_map_caption    = Location of Z\u00e1k\u00e1ny\n| pushpin_mapsize        = \n| coordinates            = {{coord|46.26672|16.94310|region:HU|display=inline,title}}\n| website                = {{URL|http://www.zakany.hu/|Z\u00e1k\u00e1ny's Official website}}\n}}\n\n'''Z\u00e1k\u00e1ny''' ({{lang-hr|Zakon / \u017dakanj}}) is a village in [[Hungary]] which is located in \n[[Somogy County|Somogy]] County next to the [[Croatia]]n border.\n\n==Location of Z\u00e1k\u00e1ny==\nLocated in Southern [[Transdanubia]], next to the [[Croatia]]n border and river [[Dr\u00e1va]].\n\nNearest Cities:\n\n[[Csurg\u00f3]]:16&nbsp;km\n\n[[Nagykanizsa]]:20&nbsp;km\n\n==History of Z\u00e1k\u00e1ny==\n[[Kingdom of Hungary]] village,The first mention of Z\u00e1k\u00e1ny was in 1227 in the middle of the [[Mongol invasion of Europe]] when Z\u00e1k\u00e1ny was called Zacun. In 1309 the people changed the village's name to Zakaan. The first refer to the village's castle was in 1325. In the 14th century (1332) the village had a parish.\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.google.com/maps/place/Z%C3%A1k%C3%A1ny,+8852/@46.2623649,16.9372857,13403m/data=!3m1!1e3!4m5!3m4!1s0x47689b5344af26e5:0x19c45474d45bf1e2!8m2!3d46.2545763!4d16.9488786 Satellite map (Hungarian)]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Csurg\u00f3 District}}\n{{Somogy}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zakany}}\n[[Category:Populated places in Somogy County]]\n[[Category:Croatia\u2013Hungary border crossings]]\n\n\n{{Somogy-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Z%C3%A1k%C3%A1ny"}
